Utilize pip to install the psycopg2 library (a PostgreSQL database library). Be sure to first create and activate a virtualenv before installing the package.

cloud_user@claudio2c:~$ mkdir venvs
cloud_user@claudio2c:~$ python3.6 -m venv venvs/pg
cloud_user@claudio2c:~$ source venvs/pg/bin/activate
(pg) cloud_user@claudio2c:~$ pip install psycopg2
